{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01S1DYW55EWuuQpxTnth3dfd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The problem might be that with keyFile authentication, the `--auth` flag is implied by `--keyFile`. And when keyFile is used, the localhost exception might work differently. \n\nActually, looking more carefully at the MongoDB documentation for keyFile + localhost exception:\n> When using keyFile authentication, the localhost exception does not apply.\n\nThis could be the issue! When keyFile is used for inter-node authentication, the localhost exception is disabled.\n\nSo the admin user was never created. How was the replica set initialized then? Maybe through some other method.\n\nLet me look at the entire startup sequence in the logs more carefully:","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1113,"cache_read_input_tokens":43531,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1113},"output_tokens":32,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"043a2d23-43fd-4cae-9ff8-4e09274ee961","uuid":"82c65c71-a76a-4426-933e-21383da096d1","request_id":"req_011CbyL2BisK9JLfWEhuZZWD"}
