{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01VUVXq3j9N8ZsFwZ1PoknQM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The replica set is now scaled to 5 members with no disruption:\n\n| Member | State | Health |\n|---|---|---|\n| `mongodb-replica-0` | PRIMARY | 1 |\n| `mongodb-replica-1` | SECONDARY | 1 |\n| `mongodb-replica-2` | SECONDARY | 1 |\n| `mongodb-replica-3` | SECONDARY | 1 |\n| `mongodb-replica-4` | SECONDARY | 1 |\n\n**What was done:**\n1. Scaled the `mongodb-replica` StatefulSet from 3 → 5 replicas — Kubernetes provisioned PVCs and started the two new pods with the same image/keyfile config.\n2. Once both new pods were `Running`, added them to the replica set via `rs.add()` on the PRIMARY — MongoDB then sync'd data to each new member via initial sync.\n3. The primary never changed and the existing three members stayed healthy throughout, preserving availability and data integrity."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":540,"cache_read_input_tokens":57020,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":540},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"043a2d23-43fd-4cae-9ff8-4e09274ee961","uuid":"1b675498-a8ec-4bf3-9354-93baf432c6c9","request_id":"req_011CbyL6x1zjbvLVyTXrrfS9"}
